{
  "texts": [
    "In essence, the distinction between human cognition, which operates at a higher level of comprehension, and complex convolutional neural networks with lower-level learning processes represents a watershed moment in the vision-based domain [213].",
    "We consolidate the active research areas previously detailed in relevant sections and illustrated in Fig. 15.",
    "Predefined concept datasetOne of the primary requirements in a human-understandable learning procedure is the creation of a predefined concept-supported dataset.",
    "Creating concept datasets, on the other hand, is currently one of the most significant challenges in the concept-supported interpretation task.",
    "This is because the significant progress made to date in generating large training datasets, such as ImageNet, CIFAR10, and MNIST, is based on pixel and lower-level learning procedures, rather than the human-understandable approach."
  ]
}